[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The recipe demonstrates strong clinical accuracy: validated screening instruments (C-SSRS, PHQ-9, GAD-7, AUDIT, EPDS) are correctly identified and scoped; evidence-based modalities (CBT, behavioral activation, DBT skills, ACT, motivational interviewing) and Stanley-Brown safety planning are appropriately referenced; 988 (launched July 2022), 42 CFR Part 2, and FDA-authorized DTx examples (reSET-O for OUD, Somryst for insomnia, EndeavorRx) are factually correct; population exclusions (primary psychotic-spectrum, active inpatient, minors in adult deployments) and scope restrictions for trauma/ED/SUD are clinically appropriate; the crisis-pathway anchor-route-surface-bridge pattern matches current evidence-based digital crisis-care practice; the companion-pattern avoidance discipline reflects documented harm in the broader category. Architectural soundness is thorough: ten-stage decomposition; consistent Bedrock Agents + Knowledge Bases + Guardrails pattern with prior chapter 11 recipes; separate KMS keys for sensitive-disclosure and crisis-event stores; HealthLake for consent-gated FHIR chart context; Step Functions for warm-handoff workflow; Connect for licensed-clinician routing with bridge-and-stay; per-cohort monitoring; graceful-degradation paths preserving crisis-resource routing. Security considerations are mental-health-calibrated: customer-managed KMS with blast-radius separation, Object Lock compliance mode sized to longest of HIPAA/state-mental-health/42 CFR Part 2/FDA SaMD obligations, VPC/PrivateLink for back-office traffic, CloudTrail data events on sensitive resources, BAA scope, state-specific mental-health-record statutes, mandatory-reporting routing. Prioritized findings are embedded as explicit HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW review items (S1-S6 for security/governance, A1-A8 for architecture, N1-N2 for lower-priority follow-ups) with concrete remediation steps including content-as-code lifecycle, false-negative-rate launch gate under 2%, separate-KMS sensitive-disclosure surface, per-cohort launch-gate monitoring, warm-handoff workforce capacity sizing, outcome-correlation pipeline, faithfulness-check verifier, DR topology with crisis-pathway integrity, multi-language launch gate, accessibility conformance, EventBridge idempotency keys, tool-surface contract management, IAM resource-based policies, and prompt-injection defense with mental-health-specific jailbreak corpus. The 'Why This Isn't Production-Ready' and 'Honest Take' sections explicitly call out the twelve traps and the dominant licensed-clinician workforce cost, which matches real-world deployment experience."}